      "Micropaleontology studies мicroscopic organisms and fragments organism past of the geological times or their structure, biology, genetically communication, and their time and expansion spreading. The creatures being studied have are small in sizes, has special method of sampling and technical process, can be found in mass, practical value them for biostratigraphy. Micro paleontological development has 4 phases.   I phase: XIX century first middle. II phase: XIX century middle and XX century first half.   III phase: XX century starts from 1920’s. IV phase: started in 1950.   To acknowledge main representatives of micro paleontology as Diatomeae, Charophyta, Coccolithophorales, Chitinozoa, Foraminifera, Radiolaria, Ostracodiodes, Conodonta main concept about creatures, representatives of main group section, their preserved condition, method to distinguish them from stones, distinguish by microscope, determine, to write, to draw, their stratigraphy importance, and it’s dispersion.",
